    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1858-05-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1858-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="116" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d116">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 71.</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Edward Everett</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Campbell</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Boston</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1858-05-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 29, 1858.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>As the radical principle of the boundary is the forty-ninth degree of
                            latitude, and the only reason for departing from it was to give the
                            whole of Vancouver’s Island to the party acquiring the largest part of
                            it, the deflection from the forty-ninth degree southward should be
                            limited to that object, and the nearest channel adopted which fulfills
                            the above conditions.<seg type="margin">Mr. Everett on the channel of
                                the treaty.</seg>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>EDWARD EVERETT.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Archibald Campbell</hi>, Esq.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
